{
  "text": "where in the second step we used the fact that |y \u2212 x| \u2264 |y| + |x| \u2264 |y| + |y| \u2212 1 \u2264 2|y|. The last integral is finite as d > 3\u03b1/2 and X has finite \u03b2-moment for any \u03b2 < \u03b1 (see [CITATION_1] Example 25.10] ).",
